<HEADLINE> Pak Apex Court Issues Supplementary Cause list </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Supreme Court
today issued a supplementary cause list fixing petition hearings
for Tuesday and a 15-member full court bench will hear the cases
regarding the appointment of Chief Justice.
</P>
<P>
There was no hearing of any case in the apex court today. The
full court bench was to hear the cases about the appointment of
Justice Sajjad Ali Shah as chief justice whereas another bench
headed by Sajjad Ali Shah was to hear the case on the contempt of
court.
</P>
<P>
Submitting his arguments on November 28 in the contempt case,
the prime minister's counsel S. M. Zafar had argued that because
of the judgment of the three-member Supreme Court bench at Quetta,
the status of the chief justice had become disputed.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he proposed that all judges of the Supreme Court
should first sit together and decide the matter before other cases
are taken up.  
</P>
</TEXT>
