<HEADLINE> 36 People Killed in Cyclonic Storms in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 1 (Xinhua) -- At least 36 people were
killed and 50 others injured in India's different parts of eastern
Uttar Pradesh in the wake of a major cyclonic storm late Sunday
night, official sources said here this evening.
</P>
<P>
The high speed storm lasted about six hours. Power and
telephone lines were disrupted, hundreds of houses blown down,
cattle heads killed and standing crops of potato and mustard
damaged in the cyclone and heavy rains.
</P>
<P>
Rescue and relief operations were in full swing in the
storm-hit areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
