<HEADLINE> Nepal, Germany to Cooperate on Poverty Alleviation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Nepal and Germany have
confirmed poverty alleviation as the overall aim of their
development cooperation, Nepal's RSS news agency said today.
</P>
<P>
After ending their annual negotiations here today, the two
countries decided to give priority to Nepal's urban and rural
development, development of the private sector, health, family
planning and infrastructure, in particular hydropower and
alternative energy, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
The German delegation confirmed that its government will
provide a grant assistance of some 36.6 million U.S. dollars to
implement various development projects in Nepal in 1997.
</P>
<P>
And the German government, depending on the approval of the
1998 budget, will provide additional assistance to cover the
foreign exchange component of the Middle Marsyangdi Hydroelectric
Project.
</P>
<P>
Germany is a member of the Nepal Aid Group.  
</P>
</TEXT>
