<HEADLINE> Egypt: Israeli Troop Pullback Plan Ambiguous </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Egypt today called Israel's plan
to withdraw troops from the West Bank as "ambiguous" and
"tactical."
</P>
<P>
It does not address the grievances of the Palestinians, and
will not push forward the peace process, Egyptian Foreign Minister
Amr Moussa told the press following meeting with an Israeli envoy.
</P>
<P>
Israel's Foreign Ministry Secretary General Eitan Ben Tsor
briefed him on the Israeli cabinet's decision to pull back troops
from the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
He conveyed to Moussa a message from Israeli Foreign Minister
David Levy, which Moussa said does not come up with a "specific"
plan.
</P>
<P>
"The peace process cannot be salvaged via proposals that lack
credibility ... especially when it comes to core issues such as
redeployment, settlements," Moussa added.
</P>
<P>
Israel's cabinet Sunday approved a plan to pull back troops
from the West Bank, but set no date and extent of the withdrawal.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian side has said to reject the plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
