<HEADLINE> Extra Loss of 40,000 Building Jobs in East Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 1 (Xinhua) -- A loss of additional 40,000 jobs
in the construction sector in eastern Germany is expected next
year due to continuing overcapacity in the industry and rising
number of foreign workers, according to a top industry official
today.
</P>
<P>
Investment in the sector would at the same time be reduced by 3
percent, Wilhelm Kuechler, vice president of the Federation of the
German Building Industry, said in a speech in Berlin.
</P>
<P>
From 1995 to 1998 in the east, according to him, an estimated
100,000 jobs would be lost in the recession-hit construction
industry, which used to be the economic driving force in the area.
</P>
<P>
The extra loss of building jobs in the east is expected to
worsen unemployment in Germany, which is likely to hit a new
historic high of 5 million in winter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
