<HEADLINE> Flood Sweeps Away 100 Homes in W. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Flood spilled out of rivers in
the west of Uganda swept away at least 100 homes, leaving some
1,000 people homeless, "The New Vision" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Rivers of Mpanga and Muguzu burst in Fort Portal town,
Bandibagyo district, the report added.
</P>
<P>
Franeis Onyai, the chief administrative officer of Bandibugyo
district, said yesterday that heavy rains destroyed property and
crops worth millions of Uganda Shilling.
</P>
<P>
Torrential rain in recent weeks caused flood that makes the
roads in the district impassable, he said.
</P>
<P>
Landslides blocked several parts on highway from Fort Portal
to Mubande, the report said. 
</P>
