<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Licenses Private Company to Explore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 1 (Xinhua)-- An agreement was signed
here today between the Ethiopian government and a private company
for the exploration of gold, base metals and associated minerals
in Oromiya region of southern Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued by the Ministry of Mines
and Energy, JCI (Ethiopia) P.L.C., a private company, is licensed
to explore minerals in Werseti-Gudba and Chambi areas of the
region.
</P>
<P>
The agreement gives exclusive right to explore for gold, base
metals and associated minerals in the areas for the coming three
years exploration period.
</P>
<P>
The company will spend a minimum of 2.22 million US Dollars
during the three years exploration activity within 30 days from
the signing of the agreement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
