<DOCNO> XIE19971202.0042 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Recommends Raising of Iraqi Oil Export Amount </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary-General
Kofi Annan today recommended to the Security Council the raising
of the Iraqi oil export amount so that Iraq can buy more supplies
for its people, UN spokesman Eckhard Fred told reporters in
today's noon brief.
</P>
<P>
But the spokesman did not provide a figure of how much the
secretary-general had proposed to increase.
</P>
<P>
In his latest report to the Security Council, Annan said the 2
billion U.S. dollars worth of oil that Iraq is currently allowed
to sell over every six months to buy food and medicine for its
people is inadequate.
</P>
<P>
Annan said the humanitarian needs of the Iraqi people, under
sanctions since 1990, are urgent, drawing on surveys showing that
children are underfed and underweight and life expectancy is
dropping among adults.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent report of the U.N. Children'd Fund, the
one-year oil-for-food program has not made an appreciable dent in
the well-being of infants under five years of age.
</P>
<P>
The oil-for-food program, which was started to implement last
December, allows Iraq to sell 2 billion dollars worth of oil every
six months to purchase humanitarian supplies under strict UN
supervision with contracts approved by a Security Council's
sanctions committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971202.0043 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-01 19:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Envoy to Discuss Accession Talks with Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The Commissioner of the
European Union (EU) for External Affairs Hans Van den Broek
arrived in Cyprus today to discuss with the government and the
Turkish Cypriots on the country's accession talks with the EU.
</P>
<P>
Speaking upon his arrival, Van den Broek said that EU members
and the European Commission have attached great importance to
seeking ways the Turkish Cypriots are represented in the entry
talks.
</P>
<P>
"We all hope obviously that the membership (of Cyprus in the
EU) will benefit both communities of the island," he said.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus, an eastern Mediterranean island, submitted in 1990 its
application to the European Union for full membership, and the two
sides will begin to negotiate the issue early next year.
</P>
<P>
But the Turkish Cypriots have opposed the decision, and walked
out of the negotiations with the government to resolve the
protracted Cyprus problem.
</P>
<P>
The Cypriot government has proposed the Turkish Cypriots join
the delegation for the entry talks.
</P>
<P>
Van den Broek came here one week before an EU summit, which is
believed to discuss the enlargement issue concerning Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
He said that he is not optimistic that the way of participation
by the Turkish Cypriot can be formulated during his two-day visit.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into a Greek Cypriot-controlled south
and a Turkish Cypriot-controlled north since 1974 when Turkish
troops took over the northern third of the island following a
failed pro-Athens coup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
