<HEADLINE> Canada's Economy Grows Slightly in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Canada's gross domestic product
(GDP) grew 0.2 percent in September following a pause in August,
Statistics Canada said today.
</P>
<P>
Combined with a strong gain in July, this raised production 1.2
percent in the third quarter, the federal statistics agency said.
</P>
<P>
Robust wholesale trade, which rose 1.9 percent, accounted for a
large portion of the GDP growth.
</P>
<P>
Manufacturing and wholesaling accounted for about 45 percent of
the overall gain for a third consecutive quarter, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Sales of machinery and equipment, notably computers and
software packages, remained high in September.
</P>
<P>
Sales of grain, beverages, drug and tobacco products and
construction materials also contributed significantly to the
advance, the agency said. 
</P>
