<HEADLINE> New Deal Signed to Settle Confusion on Olympics Kit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- A new deal was signed to settle
confusion on kit in the Olympic Games on Tuesday in Lausanne,
Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The International Olympic Committee (IOC) made an agreement
with the World Federation of Sporting Goods Industry (WFSGI),
aiming to slove one of the biggest problems of the Games.
</P>
<P>
Currently, sponsors are always facing dilemma of supplying
national team kit and shoes and clothing for individual
competitors.
</P>
<P>
The new deal ensures a final say of kits worn by competitors
for National Olympic Committee (NOC).
</P>
<P>
"It is up to the NOC to enforce the arrangement," said IOC
marketing expert Dick Pound.
</P>
<P>
The IOC also claimed its patent right of advertising using of
the five Olympic rings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
