<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong share prices rose
1.81 percent today amid stabilizing interbank rates and sharp
gains on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index gained 465.47 points to close today's
trading at 11,216.35, the highest in a month's time.
</P>
<P>
The value of turnover amounted to 13,873 million HK dollars
(1,778 million U.S. dollars), up from Monday's 5,760 million HK
dollars (738 million U.S. dollars). Today's turnover was also the
highest in a month.
</P>
<P>
The market rose 130.77 points, or 1.21 percent, to open at
10,881.65 at the opening bell in the morning today.
</P>
<P>
The market gained 449.50 points, or 4.18 percent, to close at
11,200.38 at the finish of the morning session.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index rose 224 points, or 2.13 percent, to close
at 10,750.88 Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
