<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan President Decides to Resign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani President Farooq
Leghari said here today he has decided to resign in order to end
the ongoing constitutional crisis involving the executive and the
judiciary.
</P>
<P>
While announcing his resignation, he said that the
constitutional crisis "is self-created, unnecessary and hurtful"
to the nation.
</P>
<P>
"I have decided to resign for the supremacy of the judiciary
and the constitution of the country," Leghari told a news
conference this afternoon, adding an official announcement of his
resignation will be released soon.
</P>
<P>
Leghari, who assumed his office four years ago, announced his
resignation hours after his meeting with the powerful Chief of the
Army Staff General Jahangir Karamat, who has been acting as the
mediator in the confrontation between Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif
and Chief Justice Sajjad Ali Shah in the past few weeks.
</P>
<P>
Leghari said he "has no other option but to resign from the
Presidency" because he declined to disqualify the Chief Justice as
required by the government.
</P>
<P>
"It is a sad day for Pakistan and for the constitution,"
Leghari told the crowded news conference at the Presidential
House.
</P>
<P>
"I will not dissolve the National Assembly, I will not do this
again in my life," he said. "If I will, I can do it in seconds."
</P>
<P>
"I have decided to resign for the supremacy of the institution
and the constitution of the country," said Leghari, who dissolved
the government led by then prime minister Benazir Bhutto in
December last year.
</P>
<P>
The nerve-wracking tussle between Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif
and Chief Justice Sajjad reached its climax today when Sajjad
suspended this morning the 13th Amendment to the Constitution
passed by the two houses of the Parliament in April, which clipped
the presidential power to dismiss the elected government.
</P>
<P>
However, minutes after Sajjad's order, a rival 10-member bench
of the Supreme Court declared his order invalid because he has
been under suspension. 
</P>
</TEXT>
