The Wall Street Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- Hours after announcing an agreement with the International
Monetary Fund on a support package for South Korea, the government
said a final accord hadn't been reached, knocking the country's
jittery markets lower and raising fears Seoul is resisting crucial
financial reforms. 
