<HEADLINE> China Becoming Exporter Of Airplanes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- China has exported 96 aircraft
since 1986, according to an international civil aviation
conference that opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese-built Yun-12, Yun-7, and Yun-8 have earned 300
million US dollars from exports, mostly to developing countries.
</P>
<P>
The first to be exported was the Yun-12, which was sold to Sri
Lanka in 1986. The plane is designed for both passengers and cargo
and has been certified by China, the US, and Britain.
</P>
<P>
More than 80 percent of China's civil aviation exports were
Yun-12s. Sources say that Chinese planes are reliable, and that
China provides good after-sale service. 
</P>
