<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blast Of Cold Air Hits South China's Semi-Tropical Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Temperatures on China's island
province of Hainan were closer to normal today thanks to a blast
of cold air that hit this island early this morning.
</P>
<P>
The cool air brought temperatures down to 15 to 20 degrees
centigrade, the normal temperature for this time of year, and
making it cloudy and overcast with light rain.
</P>
<P>
The weather will continue for this week, and will have an
effect on the local vegetable crop, said Duan Li, of the Hainan
Meteorological Observatory.
</P>
<P>
Warm air stayed over the island for the month of November,
bringing little rain and high temperatures, which hit 33 degrees
in the last ten days.  
</P>
</TEXT>
