<HEADLINE> OIC Expert Meeting Opens in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The expert meeting for the
eighth summit of the Organization of Islamic Conference (OIC)
was inaugurated this afternoon by a representative of the OIC
Secretary General Izzidine Al-Iraki.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening session, head of meeting, Iranian
Deputy Foreign Minister for International affairs Mohammad Javad
Zarif stressed that the Islamic countries should strengthen the
unity and cooperation among them under the new conditions after
the cold war.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Islamic countries are facing various
problems such as "the occupation of Jerusalem" by Israel, the
issues of the Palestinians, Afghanistan and Bosnia-Herzegovina,
which should be solved collectively by the Islamic countries.
</P>
<P>
With unity among the Islamic countries, Zarif said, the
Muslim world can reach the goals of peace, tranquility and
development and promote bilateral, multilateral and regional
cooperations.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that experts from the OIC member states
would coordinate with each other to work out the resolutions and
statements for the OIC summit to be held here on December 9-11.
</P>
<P>
More than 250 experts from 54 OIC member states attended
today's session and soon after the inaugural ceremony they
started to discuss the agenda for the OIC ministerial meeting
and some 150 resolutions for the OIC summit.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the issues of unity among Islamic
countries, the stalled Middle East peace process and economic
cooperation among OIC members would be on the top agenda of the
OIC summit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
