<HEADLINE> China Preparing For Spring Festival Transportation Load </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- China's Public Security
Ministry held a meeting here today to make arrangements for the
upcoming Spring Festival transportation problems.
</P>
<P>
The traditional Lunar New Year festival, which falls on January
28 next year, is the time for Chinese families to hold a
reunion. The ministry says that there will be a very large
movement of people this holiday season.
</P>
<P>
Those present at the meeting decided that the ministry will
tighten vehicles controls during the season, and special passes
will be issued to buses carrying more than 12 people, as part of
efforts to guarantee the safety of passengers, a ministry
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry says that rural vehicles and illegally modified
trucks will not be allowed to carry passengers during the festival
season. 
</P>
