<HEADLINE> Social Science Research In Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, November 2 (Xinhua) -- The Guangxi Academy of Social
Sciences in Nanning, the capital of the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region, celebrated its 20th anniversary of founding here today.
</P>
<P>
"The academy has set up 10 research centers in the past 20
years," its president, Zhan Hongsong, said, and its 180
researchers and experts have made a great effort to develop it
into an influential social science researcher in Southeast Asian
countries and ethnic groups in Guangxi.
</P>
<P>
The academy has published 300 academic books and periodicals
and has presented 4,000 research papers and reports, 180 of which
won national and provincial prizes, Zhan said.
</P>
<P>
To better serve the local economy, the academy has also had 106
research projects, which provided ideas and solutions and promoted
exchanges and co-operation between the local economy and
neighboring countries and regions.  
