<HEADLINE> Chirac Calls on EU to Reform Institutions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 2 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
today called on the European Union (EU) to reform its institutions
before the enlargement of the union takes effect, according to Agence
France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
Chirac made the statement at a joint press conference with
Spanish Prime Minister Jose Maria Aznar and French Prime Minister
Lionel Jospin at the end of the second French-Spanish summit held
in Salamanque, Spain.
</P>
<P>
Chirac said the EU summit in Luxembourg on December 12-13,
which will discuss the enlargement of the union to central and
eastern European countries, is very important because it launches
the process that will allow "the European family to live in
democracy, stability and peace.
</P>
<P>
"We should have the courage to reform our institutions before
the enlargement takes effect," said Chirac. "Our institutions,
which were adapted to six member countries, don't work very well
with 15, and will absolutely be incapable of ensuring the
responsibility of the union of 20 to 25 (members)." 
</P>
</TEXT>
