<HEADLINE> 70 Militants Killed in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Algerian security forces,
which besieged two villages in the province of Blida, 50
kilometers south of Algiers, killed 70 Islamic militants during an
eight-day operation.
</P>
<P>
For eight days, Algerian security forces supported by
helicopters have been encircled the villages of Al-Marakishia and
Al-Marga in the Blida province, two bases used by a large group
of suspected Islamic militants, local newspaper Al-Khaber
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted an Algerian security source as saying that
during the operation in the village of Marakishia, the security
forces discovered 10 deep tunnels constructed with reinforced
concrete, as well as some documents and provocative leaflets.
</P>
<P>
It also quoted a number of officers participating in
the operation as saying that Algerian security forces were
incessantly rocketing hideouts of the militants and they
have barred all way out in the two villages in order to make it
impossible for the militants to escape this time.
</P>
<P>
A total of 75,000 people have been reportedly killed in
violence during the five-year-old insurgency in Algeria.
</P>
