<HEADLINE> China to Attend Four-Party Talks on Korean Peninsula </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- China will play a "constructive
role" in the first formal meeting of the four-party talks on the
issue of the Korean Peninsula, Foreign Ministry Spokesman Tang
Guoqiang said here today.
</P>
<P>
Tang told a press conference that the meeting is scheduled for
December 9 in Geneva, Switzerland, and Chinese Vice-Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan will take part in the meeting at the head of
the Chinese government delegation.
</P>
<P>
The four parties include the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea (DPRK), the Republic of Korea (ROK), China and the United
States.
</P>
<P>
"The start of the four-party talks represents an important step
of positive significance in the Korean Peninsula peace process,"
Tang said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the establishment of a peninsular peace mechanism
through the four-party talks comply with the interests of all
parties by helping maintain peace and stability there.
</P>
<P>
Tang went on to say that "the Chinese side hopes that the
parties concerned will make positive efforts together for the
early realization of the objectives of the talks in the spirit of
equal participation, patient consultation, seeking common ground
while setting aside differences and making progress in a gradual
and incremental manner."
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese side will continue to work in close cooperation
with the relevant parties and play a constructive role in
promoting constant progress in the talks," the spokesman said.
</P>
