made a fierce contest with the quick Brazilians in an expected
aggressive game with a handful of free-kicks.
</P>
<P>
When the relentless Brazilians found themselves in the off-side
traps, the Germans struck ahead at last.
</P>
<P>
Andreas Moeller's free-kick in the 34th minute found Stephane
Chapuisat, who cut through down to the right. Michael Zorc, who
was unmarked in the left, collected Chapuisat's cross and drove
home a left-footer from close range.
</P>
<P>
After the break, the two sides played even with both sides
squandering a dozen of scoring opportunities until defender Vito
was flashed a second yellow in the 77th minute and Cruzeiro had to
played with one-man down on the pitch.
</P>
<P>
The Europen champions popped up their firepowers ten minutes
later and matchmaker Moeller looped over Cruzeiro's goalkeeper
Dida, who stopped Decheiver's powerful left-footed half-volley.
</P>
<P>
But Dortmund did managed to make benifit from the advantage of
the number of players on the pitch.
</P>
<P>
Paulo Sousa intercepted for a low pass to Moeller in the left
flank. Joerg Heinrich toed the ball to the right corner of the net
from Moller's center before Dida tried to block the shot when six
minutes left on the clock. 
</P>
