<HEADLINE> Utah's Malone Named NBA Player of Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Karl Malone of Utah Jazz was
named Tuesday NBA Player of the Week for games played from
November 24 through November 30.
</P>
<P>
Malone, who led Utah to a 3-0 record during the week, averaged
a league-high 32.0 points, 11.7 rebounds, 3.7 assists and 1.33
blocked shots in 36.7 minutes per game.
</P>
<P>
He shot 33 for 56 from the field and 30 for 38 from the free
throw line and ranked eighth in rebounding among league-leaders.
</P>
<P>
Malone began the week with 33 points, nine rebounds and seven
assists in Utah's 133-124 overtime defeat of Minnesota at the
Delta Center on November 24, and had 21 points, eight rebounds,
four assists and two steals as Jazz defeated Golden State 111-82
on November 28.
</P>
<P>
He closed the week on November 29 with a season-high 42 points,
18 rebounds and two steals in a 94-91 win at the Los Angeles
Clippers. Molone hit the the game-winning shot in that contest
and stole the ball when Clippers had a chance to tie the score in
the final seconds.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for NBA Player of the Week were Atlanta's
Christian Laettner and Dikembe Mutombo, Boston's Antoine Walker,
Cleveland's Wesley Person, Golden State's Donyell Marshall,
Indiana's Rik Smiths, Los Angeles Lakers' Eddie Jones, Miami's Tim
Hardaway, Milwaukee's Glenn Robinson, New Jersey's Kerry Kittles,
Seattle's Vin Baker and Toronto's John Wallace. 
