<HEADLINE> Eight Seeds Announced for World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Brazil, France, Germany,
Argentina, Spain, Italy, Romania and the Netherlands were the
eight seeds for the 1998 World Cup finals, the soccer's world
governing body FIFA confirmed in Marselle on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Defending champions Brazil was to be put in group A and hosts
France in group C, announced FIFA general secretary Sepp Blatter
two days before the draw.
</P>
<P>
The seeding decision was made based on previous performances in
the 1994 World Cup finals and the monthly rankings of the soccer
squads.
</P>
<P>
The rest 24 qualifiers will be bracketed into eight groups
while the World Cup organizers will manage to allocate those from
same continents into different groups. 
</P>
