<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Successful In Controlling Spread Of AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Beijing has been successful in
controlling the spread of AIDS, with only 8 new cases reported
this year, according to the Municipal Bureau of Health.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Mayor Lin Wenyi says that all of society should be made
aware of the need to prevent the spread of the deadly disease in
Beijing because it is an international city with frequent contact
with foreigners.
</P>
<P>
The city has spent more than eight million yuan (about one
million US dollars) on prevention and public awareness programs
since 1988, Beijing Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
The Municipal Bureau of Health says that the city has had 189
HIV/AIDS cases since 1985 when the first one was discovered in the
city, 59 of them foreigners, 75 from other parts of the country,
and 55 local residents.
</P>
<P>
The first AIDS case contracted through parental transmission in
the city, and the first case of infection among drug addicts, was
reported this year. Among the newly-reported cases, the ratio of
gay males is increasing, the report said.
</P>
<P>
China has 168 AIDS patients and 8,277 infected with HIV, more
than 70 percent of whom contracted the disease while using drugs.
</P>
</TEXT>
