<HEADLINE> DPR Korea to Compete in Nagano Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's Republic
of Korea has registered its participation in the Nagano Olympic
Winter Games next February, organisers said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
They will send in 13 athletes for speed skating, short-track
speed skating, alpine skiing and cross country events at the Games
starting on February 7, said the Nagano Olympic Organizing
Committee (NAOC).
</P>
<P>
Thus, the number of participating countries and regions reached
to 67 countries ahead of Monday's official deadline, equalling the
record number of teams in the 1994 Lillehammer Olympics where DPR
Korea was absent.
</P>
<P>
The organizing committee will continue to accept entries even
after the official deadline. 
</P>
</TEXT>
