<DOCNO> XIE19971202.0155 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigerian Soccer Squad Seeks Venables' Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria is looking forward to
signing former England coach Terry Venables to head its squad for
the World Cup finals in France next year.
</P>
<P>
Local reports quoted Nigerian Football Association chairman
Colonel Abdulmumuni Aminu as saying that he was ready to offer the
job to Venables, whose Australian side missed out on the World Cup
after losing to Iran last weekend.
</P>
<P>
"We will meet Terry as soon as possible," Abdulmumuni said.
"If Terry says yes, the job is his providing the salary he would
want is reasonable."
</P>
<P>
Abdulmumuni will be in Marseille for Thursday's World Cup draw
and is reported to be coming to London to talk with Venables.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria, the defending Olympic champion, has been without a
manager since Frenchman Philippe Troussier quit.
</P>
<P>
Venables is under contract with Australia until next July and
has been offered a contract extension. 
</P>
</TEXT>
