<HEADLINE> Jiang: Hong Kong's Prosperity to Continue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President
Jiang Zemin said here today that he believed Hong Kong will enjoy
long-term stability and prosperity with an expected economic
growth of 5 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Mexican newspaper "The Sun," Jiang
said that the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region has taken
effective measures to stabilize the Hong Kong dollar following the
recent fluctuations in the Hong Kong financial market.
</P>
<P>
