<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang: China is Mexico's All-Weather Friend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President
Jiang Zemin said here today that China is an all-weather friend of
Mexico and is willing to establish a cross-century partnership to
further all-round cooperation with that country.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks at a state dinner given in his honor by
Mexican President Ernesto Zedillo. The Chinese president arrived
in Mexico on November 29 for a four-day state visit.
</P>
<P>
Recalling that President Zedillo said in Beijing last year
Mexico was a trustworthy friend of China, Jiang said, "Today I
want to tell Mr. President that China is Mexico's all-weather
friend."
</P>
<P>
In his toast, Jiang said that since China and Mexico
established diplomatic ties 25 years ago, the two countries have
increased exchanges of high-level visits and expanded cooperation
in the fields of politics, defense, economy, trade, science and
technology, culture, parliamentary affairs and law enforcement.
</P>
<P>
China highly appreciates Mexico's support to its efforts in
safeguarding national sovereignty and in reunifying the country,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"There is a solid foundation for developing friendly relations
and cooperation between China and Mexico," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mexican President Zedillo said in his toast that his country
has been promoting its relations with China with unprecedented
efforts.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of China's role at the United Nations Security
Council, saying China represents the voice of the developing
countries.
</P>
<P>
Zedillo said that Mexico has identical views with China on many
major international issues and both countries are willing to work
together for a more equitable international order.
</P>
<P>
He said that Jiang's state visit will help forge a firm and
lasting strategic partnership.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China and Mexico all maintain that all
countries, big or small, strong or weak, rich or poor, are equal
and should work together for the establishment of a new just and
equitable international order.
</P>
<P>
"Our two countries can learn from each other because we both
have rich resources and a huge market, we both face the task of
developing national economy and improving the living standard of
the people, we both are striving for development in accordance
with our national conditions, and we both have accumulated our own
experience in national-building," he said.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to build a cross-century partnership of
all-round cooperation with Mexico, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
As China and Mexico are two major developing nations across the
Pacific, developing a long-term, all-round and stable relationship
of friendly cooperation between the two countries is not only in
their fundamental interests, but also helps promote peace and
development in the Asia-Pacific region and the world at large, he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
