<HEADLINE> Chinese President To Attend Informal ASEAN Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
is to attend informal summit meetings between China and the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) in Malaysia later
this month.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang announced here today
that at the invitation of Dr. Mahathir Mohammed, rotating chairman
of ASEAN and prime minister of Malaysia, President Jiang will
travel to Kuala Lumpur, capital of Malaysia, on December 14 to
attend the informal summit meeting between ASEAN and China, Japan
and the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
Jiang will also attend the informal summit meeting between
ASEAN and China in Kuala Lumpur, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
According to Tang, President Jiang's wife Wang Yeping and
Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen will accompany
Jiang on the trip.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that the upcoming informal summit between ASEAN and
China, Japan and ROK and that between ASEAN and China are
meetings of East Asian leaders at the turn of the century. It is
also the first summit meeting between East Asian countries and
ASEAN and between China and ASEAN in history.
</P>
<P>
He said that the summit is a "strong manifestation" of the
movement towards multi-polarization in the world after the end of
the Cold War and reflects the rise of East Asia and its
international status.
</P>
<P>
"The summit, which will be convened on the occasion of the
30th anniversary of the founding of ASEAN, will help promote
economic cooperation in the East Asian region and increase the
China-ASEAN friendly relations and cooperation," Tang said.
</P>
<P>
"It is therefore a significant event," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the meeting, leaders of ASEAN countries,
China, Japan and ROC will exchange views on the prospects of
development and regional cooperation in East Asia in the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
He said that during the meeting, President Jiang will have an
extensive exchange of views with leaders of ASEAN countries on
China-ASEAN relations, and after the meeting will issue a joint
statement on the establishment of the good-neighborly and mutual
trust partnership between China and ASEAN oriented towards the
21st century, which will bring China-ASEAN the relationship into a
new phase of development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
