<HEADLINE> Majority of HK Schools to Teach in Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The majority of the 307
schools in total in Hong Kong will use Chinese for teaching all
academic subjects in the next two years, progressing each year to
a higher level, according to a press release available here today.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a total of 100 secondary schools will continue
teaching in English in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) in the coming academic year, it added.
</P>
<P>
The Vetting Committee, set up in October, announced that the
100 schools met the requirements for using English as the medium
of instruction.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, there were calls for more mother-tongue
teaching in secondary schools, aimed at helping students learn
more effectively.
</P>
<P>
All this showed that the SAR government has paid great
attention to school teaching in both Chinese and English, with the
aim of helping improve students' practical capability.  
</P>
