<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Improved U.S.-Cuban Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President
Jiang Zemin said here today that he hoped the relations between
the United States and Cuba will be improved through dialogue on
the basis of equality.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Mexican newspaper "Excelsior," Jiang
said there are an increasing number of countries at the United
Nations which are in sympathy with Cuba and vote against the
U.S. economic embargo on Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who arrived in Mexico on November 29 for a four-day
state visit, said that the embargo does no good to Cuba, the
U.S. and the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
