<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- Bernard Kouchner, the State Secretary of Health, is working on
a plan on the treatment of drug addicts through new therapeutical
approach which allows the controlled distribution of heroin, a
therapeutical use of cannabis and an increase of the sites which
sell methadone, a potent narcotic analgesic drug which is used to
relieve severe pain. France has been carrying out a repressive law
against drug addicts since 1970, which punishes all drug addicts by
making all of them criminals or delinguents and allows judges to
give therapeutical injunctions.
</P>
<P>
-- The Spanish Supreme Court gave a severe verdict against 23
leaders of the Herri Batasuna (HB), the political wing of the Basque
separatist movement ETA, sentencing them all to seven years in
prison. The verdict cannot but revive the tension in the Basque
region of Spain. Inigo Iruin, one of the defense lawyers of the
convicted, said that he will resort to the Constitutional Tribunal
of Spain and the European Tribunal of Human Rights in protest of the
verdict.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The National Assembly voted on Monday with 267 votes for and
246 votes against the new law on nationality presented by the
Minister of Justice Elisabeth Guigou, which gives all the children
born of foreign parents in France the right to obtain French
nationality at the age of 18, as long as they have lived in France
for more than five years during the period. However, the Socialist
government failed to receive support from its Communist and
Ecologist allies, with 24 out of 26 parliament members of the
Communist Party and five out of six of the Green Party abstaining
from the vote.
</P>
<P>
-- The French public insurance group, Groupement des Assurances
Generale (GAN), has lost at least 34.5 billion francs (5.8 billion
U.S. dollars) from 1992 to 1996, if not more. The Court of Accounts
is launching an inquiry into the loss of GAN, which is reportely
engaged in some doubtful real estate affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
