<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Repeat and Correction: Parliament says Suspension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Parliamentary Secretary
Zaffar Ali shah said here today that the suspension of the 13th
Amendment to the Constitution is "illegal" and "unconstitutional."
</P>
<P>
He made the statement soon after a three-member bench headed by
Chief Justice Sajjad Ali Shah issued an order to suspend the 13th
Amendment to the Constitution.
</P>
<P>
The move by Sajjad Ali Shah was aimed at creating "chaos" in
the country, Zaffar added.
</P>
<P>
When issuing the order, Sajjad Ali Shah said that Pakistan is
on the brink of a "constitutional breakdown." He said that it is
necessary to suspend the 13th Amendment.
</P>
<P>
However, another bench of the apex court headed by Justice
Saeed Uzzman Siddiqui rejected the order and suspended the
appointment of Sajjad Ali Shah as the Chief Justice.
</P>
<P>
The three-member bench headed by Sajjad Ali Shah is now hearing
a petition on the case of the contempt of court against Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, President Farooq Leghari, who is now having a
meeting with Chief of the Army Staff General Jahangir karamat, has
called for a press conference at the Presidential House.  
</P>
</TEXT>
