<HEADLINE> Jiang: China-U.S. Summit Successful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin said here today that his recent summit meeting with
U.S. President Bill Clinton has brought China-U.S. relations to a
new stage.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Mexican newspaper "The Sun," Jiang
said his state visit to the U.S. from October 26 to November 3 was
successful in deepening understanding, broadening common ground
and promoting cooperation between China and the United States.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who arrived in Mexico on November 29 for a four-day
state visit to the country, said he and President Clinton agreed
to build a 21st century-oriented constructive strategic
partnership between the two countries in order to promote peace
and development in the world.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also reached agreement on a variety of issues,
with the U.S. reiterating its adherence to the one-China policy,
he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China will work together with the U.S. to
implement these agreements and ensure a healthy and steady
development of bilateral relations. 
</P>
