<DOCNO> XIE19971202.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Justice Ajmal Takes over Control of Supreme Court </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Justice Ajmal Mian, the
second most senior judge in Pakistan's Supreme Court, has taken
over the administrative and judicial control of the apex court.
</P>
<P>
The 10-member bench of the Supreme Court led by Justice Saeed
Uzzaman Siddiqui today ordered the President to appoint Justice
Ajmal Mian as acting Chief Justice for being the most senior judge
and in the meantime directed Mian to discharge duties of the Chief
Justice including constitution of the benches.
</P>
<P>
"Pursuant to the judicial order passed on December 2, 1997, by
a bench of this court comprising ten learned judges, I order the
fixation of roster from December 3, 1997," said an order signed by
Justice Ajmal Mian directing Registrar of the Court for
compliance.
</P>
<P>
The order came after a three-member bench headed by Chief
Justice Sajjad Ali Shah suspended the 13th Amendment to the
Constitution restoring the presidential powers to dissolve the
National Assembly and dismiss government.
</P>
<P>
However, minutes after the order by Sajjad, the rival 10-member
bench headed by Justice Siddiqui overturned the ruling, upholding
the constitutional amendment.
</P>
<P>
the rival bench at the same time also ordered the suspension of
the appointment of Sajjad Ali Shah as the Chief Justice of the
Supreme Court.
</P>
<P>
The government-judicial tussle, which has lasted for more than
three months and has intensified in recent weeks, has virtually
put Pakistan in an unprecedented constitutional crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Bar Association of the Supreme Court has expressed its
support to the suspension of the 13th Amendment of the
Constitution.
</P>
<P>
the Bar Association of the apex court in a statement today
accused the government of Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif of splitting
the Supreme Court.
</P>
<P>
However, Parliamentary Secretary Zaffar Ali Shah said the
suspension of the 13th Amendment is "illegal" and
"unconstitutional."
</P>
<P>
The move by Sajjad Ali Shah was aimed at creating "chaos" in
the country, Zaffar added.
</P>
<P>
The order by the three-member bench said, "There is complete
breakdown of the constitutional machinery and it appears that the
government is not being run according to the provisions of the
Constitution."
</P>
<P>
But the rival 10-member bench rejected the order and suspended
the appointment of Sajjad Ali Shah as the Chief Justice.
</P>
<P>
The 13th Amendment to the Constitution, which was passed by the
two Houses of the Parliament in April this year, took away the
powers of the President to dissolve the National Assembly and
dismiss government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
