<HEADLINE> Kenya Airways Profit Jumps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Kenya Airways won a 52.9
percent increase in its before-tax profit for the first half of
the current fiscal year starting from March, local press reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The national carrier earned a before-tax profit of 821 million
Shillings (13.7 million U.S. Dollars) between March and
September, compared with 537 million Shillings (nine million
Dollars) over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The company posted a turnover of 5.75 billion Shillings during
the six months compared to 5.08 billion for the same period last
year, which represented a 13.2 percent increase, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The earnings per share improved from 80 cents in the first
half of last year to 1.17 Shillings from March to September, said
the report.
</P>
<P>
During the period under review, the company's revenue
estimatedly rose to 5.7 billion Shillings (89 million U.S.
Dollars) from five billion Shillings (78 million Dollars) in the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, revenue from passenger ticket sales increased by
12.8 percent from 4.01 billion Shillings to 4.53 billion
Shillings while cargo generated 662 million Shillings, up 6.8
percent from 620 million Shillings from March to September in
1996.
</P>
<P>
The airline made a gain of 186 million Shillings on foreign
exchange movement from March to September due to the rapid
depreciation of the Shilling against the hard currencies as a
result of political unrests in the country ahead of general
elections set for December 29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
