<HEADLINE> CAPD Concludes National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Eighth National Congress of
the China Association for Promoting Democracy (CAPD) ended today
with Xu Jialu elected as chairman of the association's Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Xu, a noted Chinese linguist, joined the CAPD in 1987, and was
elected to serve as vice-chairman of the organization in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The CAPD, one of China's eight non-communist parties, was
established in 1945 and is composed mainly of intellectuals from
the fields of education, culture, publishing and science, as well
as patriotic personages from the industrial and business sectors.
</P>
<P>
The congress ended with a revised CAPD constitution, and the
election of a 187-member central committee. 
