<DOCNO> XIE19971202.0208 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Hosts Centennial Commemoration Honoring Rewi Alley </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Some 500 Chinese and foreign
personages gathered in the Great Hall of the People here today to
mark the 100th Birth Anniversary of Rewi Alley, a famous New
Zealand writer, educator and social activist.
</P>
<P>
Alley came to China in 1927. Since then, he had lived in the
country for 60 years before he passed away 10 years ago.
</P>
<P>
After his death, late Deng Xiaoping once wrote of
Alley: "Eternity to the Great Internationalist Fighter". Premier
Li Peng, in his inscription for today's commemorative meeting,
described Alley as "A Man of Lofty Merits and A Glorious Example",
while Vice-Premier Qian Qichen referred to Ally as "A Loyal
Fighter and An Ambassador of Friendship".
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China
and member of the Central Committee Secretariat, attended the
commemorative meeting. Prior to the meeting, he met with a New
Zealand delegation of noted figures, led by former
Governor-General Paul Reeves, and members of Alley's family.
</P>
<P>
Hu praised Alley's outstanding contribution to the Chinese
revolution and the nation's construction, as well as his unique
role in promoting understanding and friendship between the peoples
of China and New Zealand, and among the people throughout the
world.
</P>
<P>
The centennial meeting was sponsored by the Chinese People's
Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries. Association
President Qi Huaiyuan, Reeves and members of Alley's family
reviewed Alley's glorious life.
</P>
<P>
Alley joined other foreigners and patriotic Chinese in
establishing the Gung Ho Movement in Shanghai in 1937, at the very
beginning of the Chinese People's War of Resistance against
Japanese Aggression.
</P>
<P>
He later served as general-manager of the Association of
Chinese Industrial Cooperatives established in Wuhan in 1938. Over
3,000 cooperatives across China provided badly needed uniforms,
blankets, weapons and ammunition for soldiers at the front.
</P>
<P>
In response to Alley's suggestion, the Association of Chinese
Industrial Cooperatives resumed activities in 1983, following some
30 years of inactivity. The association proceeded to establish
more than 200 industrial cooperatives to promote the growth of
China's socialist economy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971202.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Province Increasing Wildlife Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Since the 1980s, China's
Guangdong Province has found more effective ways to protect its
wildlife by establishing special organizations at different levels
in charge of wild life protection.
</P>
<P>
The province is home to 117 wild animals that are under state
protection, and has 100 species of endangered rare plants, and 130
animal breeding centers.
</P>
<P>
It has set up 28 nature reserves measuring 187,000 hectares in
all, or 1.05 percent of the province's total area.
</P>
<P>
These reserves have done a great deal in promoting wildlife
protection, research, education, and international co-operation.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong has made March 20 to 26 the time of its annual "Bird
Festival" and "Love Birds Week" and has made November the month of
publicizing wildlife protection.
</P>
<P>
More than 4,000 cases of illegal selling of rare animals have
been dealt with since 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971202.0210 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Making Greater Profits out of Corn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- If you want to make more money
out of corn, you could do worse than studying the method of the
Lianfa Company in central China's Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
By wrapping a head of corn in a plastic coating and freezing
it, the company kept the freshness and extended marketing time by
a few months, and managed to sell half a pound of corn at 3.5 yuan
(0.42 US dollars), about the same as the price of pork. The usual
price for the same amount of corn is 0.6 to 0.7 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Lianfa, of Zhengzhou City, sold eight million head of corn from
the 1996 autumn harvest wrapped in this way in big cities like
Guangzhou and Tianjin during the Spring Festival last year.
</P>
<P>
The company has grown over 333 hectares of corn this autumn for
greater profits.
</P>
<P>
And, the good thing is that the cost is minimal, since the
wrapping costs only 0.08 yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
