<HEADLINE> Shanghai Hosts International Maritime Technology Symposium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The four-day 1997
International Maritime Technology Symposium, which opened today in
Shanghai, will focus on discussions of global maritime activities
and the host city's status as an international shipping center.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Mayor Xu Kuangdi and various high-ranking Chinese
officials from the nation's shipping sector presented speeches
covering the development of China's shipping industry, the
construction of Shanghai ports, and the city's evolution into an
International maritime center.
</P>
<P>
The symposium attracted more than 1,000 participants from 20
countries and regions, including Britain, Germany, France, Norway,
Japan, the Netherlands, China and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The four-day 1997 International Maritime Technology Exposition
also opened today.
</P>
<P>
The exposition features equipment and products manufactured by
over 600 corporations from 24 countries and regions. It will be
closed on Friday.  
