<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Singaporean Senior Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
said today that mutually beneficial Sino-Singaporean cooperation
is in the fundamental interests of the two peoples, and is
conducive to peace, stability and development in the region.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remark during a meeting with Singaporean Senior
Minister Lee Kuan.
</P>
<P>
Li extended a warm welcome to the Singaporean minister and
noted that China and Singapore established diplomatic ties seven
years ago. He pointed to the fact that bilateral relations have
witnessed substantial development, and noted increasingly active
cooperation and exchanges in various fields, as well as fruitful
results in economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Li also pointed to the financial turmoil which has hit
Southeast Asia this year, and stressed that China will continue to
strengthen reciprocal cooperation with nations in the region,
including Singapore.
</P>
<P>
He said the current situation will require concerned countries
to strengthen communications and coordinations in order to raise
friendly cooperation to a new plateau.
</P>
<P>
In response, Lee said the fact that he discovers new
achievements in China's economic construction and new progress in
the social undertakings with each successive visit to the country
is encouraging.
</P>
<P>
Various east Asian countries are facing severe difficulties
derived from the financial crisis, while China has maintained a
stable economic situation and avoided any harmful effects,
according to Lee. This demonstrates that Chinese leaders have
correctly handled policies and are truly deserving of
congratulations, said Lee.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese vice-premier briefed Lee on the success of the 15th
National Congress of the Chinese Communist Party and the nation's
reform and opening efforts.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that construction of the industrial park in Suzhou,
the largest cooperative project between the two governments, is
progressing smoothly due to the efforts of both governments.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese government attaches great importance to
building the park and will continue to offer its full support for
the project. Li also expressed hope that the two governments will
further strengthen cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
