<DOCNO> XIE19971202.0231 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World's Largest Barium Sulfate Production Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Second phase construction of
the world's largest barium sulfate production base is progressing
smoothly in southwest China's Guizhou Province and is scheduled
for completion in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimate the base, which will have an annual production
capacity of 100,000 tons of barium sulfate, will grab a 33 percent
share of the the world market.
</P>
<P>
The Hongxing Chemical Industry Company (Group) based in
Qingdao, in east China's Shandong Province, is constructing the
base at a cost of 200 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The first phase, which was completed at the cost of 100 million
yuan, entered operations last year following only 11 months of
construction.
</P>
<P>
The base produced 450,000 tons of barium carbonate valued 120
million yuan in the second half of 1996, with 90 percent output
earmarked for export.
</P>
<P>
The open-cut production base has an estimated reserve of 10
million tons of barite which is the main raw material for
manufacturing barium sulfates such as barium carbonate and
strontium carbonate used for television tubes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971202.0232 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East Chinese Harbor Gets More Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The city of Zhoushan in east
China's Zhejiang Province near the Yangtze River mouth, is
becoming a major east coast port, along with Ningbo and Wenzhou.
</P>
<P>
The city, composed of 1,300 islands and islets, has a total of
1,500 kilometers of coastline, 150 wharves, eight of
which accommodate 10,000 dwt ships, and has become one of the
country's largest transit port for oil, ore and coal. The port
handled 2,000 vessels or 12 million tons of cargo last year.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, 30 new docks added a handling capacity
of 20 million tons, and the Aoshan petroleum transit area has put
into operation three docks in recent years. It handled six million
tons of oil in the first half of this year, becoming the country's
largest oil transit center. The Majishan ore dock, which has a
250,000 ton capacity, is being built at a cost of two billion yuan
(241 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The harbor construction has attracted investors from the U.S.,
France, Australia, and the Netherland and total contracts are
worth three billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The city has opened direct routes to Shanghai, Ningbo and
Wenzhou in China, and to Japan, the U.S., Singapore, and
Malaysia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971202.0233 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Establishment of Crocodile Farms Urged in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian government
should cooperate with the international community in establishing
crocodile farms in buffer zones so as to protect both the river
reptile and people, said a wildlife official.
</P>
<P>
The official was commenting on the measures being taken by the
Sumbawanga District Council to kill crocodiles which made
frequent attacks on local residents.
</P>
<P>
Hashim Mbonde, director of Hambo Crocodile Farm, said last
weekend that he has been issued a permit by the district council
to kill about 200 crocodiles in Lake Rukwa as one of the measures
to check the growing threat of crocodile attacks, The Guardian
reported today.
</P>
<P>
"To solve the problem, the government, in collaboration with
the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations
(FAO), should encourage the local people to start crocodile
farms," he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Through cooperation with the international community, the
government could successfully establishing crocodile farms
instead of hunting them.
</P>
<P>
He said the hunting of crocodiles could endanger the species
whose population is put at 150,000.
</P>
<P>
"The number of crocodiles in Tanzania is declining, thus the
hunting exercise could make the species perish," Mbonde warned.
</P>
<P>
According to him, countries with big number of crocodiles
agreed in 1990 to encourage local people to start crocodile
farms.
</P>
<P>
The FAO is to cooperate with countries concerned to launch
crocodile farms but so far only five farms have been established
in Tanzania. They are in Dar es Salaam, Ifakara, Rukwa and
Rufiji.
</P>
<P>
Young crocodiles should be taken from the reserves in buffer
zones and be domesticated, said the wildlife official, adding
that within three years, the problem of crocodile attacks will be
resolved. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
