<HEADLINE> Transnational Group Opens Representative Office in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Asea Brown Boveri (ABB), one of
the world's largest electrical engineering groups, has opened a
representative office in Chengdu, capital of southwest China's
Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
The office will provide the group with a better understanding
of market needs in Sichuan, and will enable it to respond quickly
to local demand, according to Rolf Schaumann, president of ABB
China.
</P>
