<HEADLINE> Dhaka Signs Agreement with Tribal Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi government today
signed an historic agreement with tribal rebels, ending more than
two decades of armed conflict in the Chittagong Hill Tracts (CHT).
</P>
<P>
According to a copy of the agreement obtained by Xinhua from
the prime minister's office, a powerful regional council, holding
the status of a ministry, will be founded in charge of the CHT
affairs and it will be headed by a tribal person.
</P>
<P>
The accord was an outcome of six days of crucial peace talks
between the National Committee on Chittagong Hill Tracts (NCCHT)
formed by the government and Parbattaya Chattagram Jana Sanghati
Samity (PCJSS), the political wing of the armed rebels.  
</P>
