<HEADLINE> Anhui Witnesses Rapid Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province
expects its economic growth rate for 1997 to once again exceed the
national average of 13 percent.
</P>
<P>
The shift in the nation's economic development focus from
eastern coastal to inland areas, as well as improved
infrastructure construction, enabled Anhui to record an annual
economic growth rate of 17 percent during the 1992-1996 period.
</P>
<P>
The sectors of the province's agriculture, forestry, animal
husbandry and fisheries produced a total 1997 output value of 61
billion yuan, up 7.5 percent on 1996. The province also enjoyed a
record 1997 grain harvest of 28.5 billion kg, up 1.5 billion kg on
1996.
</P>
<P>
The added value for industrial enterprises at and above the
county level hit 55 billion yuan for the first 10 months of the
year, up 16 percent on the 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
Anhui generated over 154 billion yuan in industrial output
value during the 10 month period, with an 18 percent growth rate
exceeding both the national average and the figure for the
previous year's period.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
