<HEADLINE> Tourists Flock to Hainan Island of China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Over 304,300 foreign tourists
visited China's tropical Hainan Island on the South China Sea in the
first nine months of this year, a year-on-year rise of 31.28
percent.
</P>
<P>
Hainan province hosted a total of over 5.5 million Chinese and
foreign tourists during the period, earning more than 4.5 billion
yuan (547.3 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Tourism officials in Hainan attributed the travel industry's
growth to efforts designed to transform the island from merely a
sightseeing destination into a popular holiday resort.
</P>
<P>
Hainan Island, dubbed the "Hawaii of the Orient", features
beautiful bays with white sand beaches, hot springs and unique
ethnic folklore.
</P>
<P>
In Hainan, tourists can enjoy the ample sunshine and the blue
sea, play golf, visit wildlife sanctuaries, stay in a
hot spring sanatoriums, and visit both volcano parks and folklore
villages. 
</P>
