<HEADLINE> Sino-British JLG Holds 41st Session in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese side will abide by
the spirit of the Sino-British Joint Declaration, and will work
with the British side to fulfill the tasks of the Sino-British
Joint Liaison Group (JLG) over the next two years.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Wang Guisheng, China's chief JLG representative,
made the remarks today during the two-day 41st session of the JLG,
the group's first meeting since Hong Kong's return to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that great changes have taken place over the past
five months since Hong Kong's return. He said the smooth transfer
of power and steady transition have been realized due to bilateral
cooperation, and noted that the government of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), established five months
ago, is operating smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The original capitalist system and way of life in Hong Kong
remain unchanged, said Wang, adding that Deng Xiaoping's concept
of "one country, two systems" has been realized.
</P>
<P>
Wang went on to say that the JLG's work has entered a new phase
under new circumstances, and that the Chinese side will cooperate
with the British side in an active, friendly and down-to-earth
manner in order to fulfill the tasks of the JLG over the next two
years.
</P>
<P>
Alan Paul, chief representative for the British side, said that
Hong Kong's return and realization of "one country, two systems"
have enabled people to witness the continuation of the region's
system and way of life.
</P>
<P>
He said that joint efforts have enabled the two sides to
successfully settle the Hong Kong issue which was left over from
history. He added that the British side will make contributions to
the JLG's work over the next two years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
