<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Market Slow in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Monthly stock turnover on the
Shanghai Stock Exchange plunged 11 percent in November, according
to exchange statistics.
</P>
<P>
The market remained in a correction period with main indices
hitting new lows in November. The Composite Stock Index, the
benchmark indicator, closed the month at 1,181.16 points, down
3.45 percent on October. The SSE-30 Index, an exponent which
tracks high performance blue-chip shares, dropped 3.08 percent
from October to 3,658.85 points.
</P>
<P>
The market stars last month included China Eastern Airlines and
Shanghai Auto, with both introducing huge public offerings in
early November.
</P>
<P>
Due to the affects of neighboring markets, the index tracking
the B shares, or shares reserved for overseas investors only,
broke through the 60 point hallmark, closing November at 54.20
points, down 15.3 percent on the previous month. Trading in B
shares plunged 17 percent from October to end last month at 1.039
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Slumps also occurred on the treasury bond market during
November, with spot trading for T-bonds totaling 30.35 billion
yuan and bond repurchasing hitting 89.69 billion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
