<HEADLINE> Preferential Import Policy for Foreign-Funded Businesses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- China will extend its
preferential policy on imports for foreign-funded businesses,
according to sources of the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation (MOFTEC)
</P>
<P>
A MOFTEC press release issued today said the State Council has
granted approval for China to continue to exempt import tariffs
for equipment and materials which are part of the investment of
foreign-funded enterprises approved prior to March 31, 1996. The
exemption applies until a business imports all equipment and
materials considered part of its investment.
</P>
<P>
China introduced import tariff levies on foreign-funded
enterprises on April 1, 1996. 
