<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Expands Green Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, is improving the urban environment by
establishing more green areas.
</P>
<P>
New green areas have been established in the downtown area
following the demolition of illegally constructed apartment
buildings and houses.
</P>
<P>
Related demolition projects have been launched in 61 districts,
and 13,000 sq.m. of green space will replace structures with floor
space of 18,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
Statistics for the past five years show a 200 ha. decline in
the city's green areas due to the expansion of roads and the
construction of overpasses, subways and development zones.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou has drafted a series of regulations designed to
expand green areas and provide a clean urban environment.
</P>
<P>
It has planned to establish green areas covering 300 hectares
during 1997. 
