<HEADLINE> Exchanges Between Sichuan, Taiwan Provinces of China Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Exchanges between Sichuan
Province in southwest China and Taiwan Province in east China
have increased as relations across the Taiwan Straits improve.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have had 100 programs for exchanges of culture,
science and technology, economy, education, and public health
since 1996. And since 1987, Sichuan has hosted more than 1.7
million Taiwan compatriots who have come to visit relatives in the
most heavily populated province in China.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan now has 857 Taiwanese-funded firms, involving more than
700 million US dollars, or a fifth of the overseas investment in
the province.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan compatroits' relatives in Sichuan have set up 2,000
companies with capital from Taiwan, with registered capital of 300
million yuan (37.5 million US dollars).  
</P>
