<HEADLINE> Jiang: China is Mexico's All-Weather Friend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin said here today that China is an all-weather friend of
Mexico and is willing to establish a cross-century partnership to
further all-round cooperation with that country.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks at a state dinner given in his honor by
Mexican President Ernesto Zedillo.
</P>
<P>
Recalling that President Zedillo said in Beijing last year that
Mexico was a trustworthy friend of China, Jiang said. "Today I
want to tell Mr. President that China is Mexico's all-weather
friend."
</P>
<P>
In his toast, Jiang said that since China and Mexico
established diplomatic ties 25 years ago, the two countries have
increased exchanges of high-level visits and expanded cooperation
in the fields of politics, defense, economy, trade, science and
technology, culture, parliamentary affairs and law enforcement.
</P>
<P>
China highly appreciates Mexico's support to its efforts in
safeguarding national sovereignty and in reunifying the country,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Both China and Mexico maintain that all countries, big or
small, strong or weak, rich or poor, are equal and should work
together for the establishment of a new just and equitable
international order, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"Our two countries can learn from each other because we both
have rich resources and huge markets, we both face the task of
developing national economy and improving the living standard of
our people, we both are striving for development according to our
own national conditions, and we both have accumulated our own
experience in nation-building," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to build a cross-century partnership for
all-round cooperation with Mexico, he said.
</P>
<P>
As China and Mexico are two major developing nations across the
Pacific, Jiang said, developing a long-term, all-round and stable
relationship of friendship and cooperation is not only in their
own fundamental interests but also helps promote peace and
development in the Asia-Pacific region and the world at large.
</P>
</TEXT>
