<HEADLINE> Chinese Arts Show Opens in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 1 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese Arts Show opened today
in the Red Palace here to showcase tens of fine artifacts typical
of the Chinese traditional culture.
</P>
<P>
In the entire month ahead, visitors will be able to see a
parade of paintings, pottery and porcelain, lacquerware, jade
carving, double-faced embroidery and cloisonne.
</P>
<P>
In addition, there are the so-called "four treasures of the
study," or writing brush, inkstick, inkslab and paper.
</P>
<P>
Dai Chao, head of the Chinese Traditional Culture Development
Center, said the event was to help the Russian people understand
the Chinese culture and the Sino-Russian friendship to grow.
</P>
<P>
As the organizer of the show, the Moscow-based center brought
students attending its martial arts classes to perform martial art
practices in front of the guests invited to the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Those present included Chinese Cultural Attache Jia Fuyun and
other diplomats, representatives of the Russian-Chinese Friendship
Association and the municipal government, and Russian sinologists.
</P>
<P>
His organization, founded in 1994, is dedicated to the
promotion of traditional Chinese culture in Russia, Dai said.
</P>
<P>
Over years, he noted, the center has provided training courses
in Chinese martial arts, qigong, calligraphy, painting,
traditional Chinese medicine and the Chinese language. 
</P>
