<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 115,000 Sri Lankans Get Foreign Jobs This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 2 (Xinhua) -- A total of 115,000 Sri Lankans
have obtained overseas jobs from January to October this year, the
Sri Lanka Bureau of Foreign Employment (SLBFE) said here today.
</P>
<P>
The SLBFE said that in the first half of this year, about
66,720 foreign jobs were granted to Sri Lankans who registered
with the bureau.
</P>
<P>
The bureau said that 710,000 Sri Lankans are employed in the
Middle East and other Asian regions at present.
</P>
<P>
Each year they send back remittances exceeding 47 billion
Rupees (797 million U.S. dollars), according to statistics by the
bureau.
</P>
<P>
The government is considering to expand overseas employment
opportunities for locals by 20 percent in order to take in more
foreign exchange earnings as well as to reduce the pressure of
unemployment.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rate has been brought down to around ten
percent so far this year. Last year the rate was 14.5 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
