<HEADLINE> Russia Reports Rapid Increase in HIV Cases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The Center of AIDS Prevention
today reported 7,005 HIV carriers in Russia in the 10 years up to
December 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The center's director said the actual figure could be nine
times higher and would increase to 1 million by 2000.
</P>
<P>
The number of people tested HIV positive in 1996 was 2.5 times
than that in 1995 while in the first 11 months of this year it
went up three times over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the rapid increase in the number of HIV carriers
to drug abuse and prostitution and called on the government to
crack down on drug trafficking and prostitution. 
</P>
