<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Mexico Agree to Forge Trans-Century Partnership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President
Jiang Zemin and his Mexican counterpart, Ernesto Zedillo, today
agreed that China and Mexico should establish a partnership of
all-round cooperation crossing into the next century.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders reached the agreement during their talks here
at the presidential residence. They maintained that such a
relationship is of great importance in enhancing the overall
strength of developing countries, and in establishing a new
international political and economic order.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and Zedillo also agreed on four points for advancing
China-Mexico ties, including increasing exchanges of high level
visits and promoting political cooperation; enhancing economic and
trade cooperation on the basis of equality and mutual benefit;
conducting all-round cooperation and strengthening friendship, and
cooperating closely and supporting each other on international
issues, particularly strengthening their coordination and
cooperation in the United Nations and in the Asia-Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) forum.
</P>
<P>
During their talks, the two leaders reviewed the development of
China-Mexico relations in the past 25 years and spoke highly of
the growth of economic and trade ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president noted that with concerted efforts by both
sides, bilateral economic and trade ties have been gradually
promoted while exchanges in the fields of science and technology,
culture, defense, parliament and law enforcement have increased.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders agreed that they needed to explore new avenues
of economic cooperation and further open their markets.
</P>
<P>
Having exchanged visits within a year, the Chinese and Mexican
heads of state have established a close working relationship and
personal friendship, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said China and Mexico, as two developing powers that
carry weight, and as members of APEC, enjoy political stability
and economic development and bear a major impact on regional and
international issues.
</P>
<P>
The broad common ground shared by the two countries is a solid
foundation for the further development of their friendly relations
of cooperation, Jiang added.
</P>
<P>
Zedillo said China is playing an increasingly important role in
the international arena and Mexico is willing to establish closer
ties of cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He hoped Mexico and China would increase consultation and
coordination on international issues.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told Zedillo that China supports Mexico's proposal for
holding a special session of the United Nations General Assembly
on drugs next year. China attaches great importance to cooperation
with other countries including Mexico in this field.
</P>
<P>
China has decided to send relief goods to Mexico's tornado-hit
areas to help residents there rebuild their home at an earlier
date, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Zedillo said Jiang's on-going visit will bring Mexico-China
relations into a new stage of development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
