<HEADLINE> Myanmar Suspended Imports from Thailand at Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar has suspended the
imports from Thailand via the Mae Sot border checkpoint in
Thailand's Tak province.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar's Myawaddy local authorities last weekend ordered the
suspension without giving any explanation, leaving consumer goods,
construction materials, auto parts worth millions of baht from
Thailand stranded at Mae Sot district, local newspapers said
today.
</P>
<P>
Thai customs officials said that Myanmar suspended its imports
through the checkpoint pending the improvement of its tariff
collection system after the Myanmar currency weakened against the
baht and the U.S. dollar late last month.
</P>
<P>
The checkpoint was expected to return to normal this Friday,
the officials added.  
</P>
