<HEADLINE> Smooth European EMU Entry Possible: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The European economies will
develop rapidly in the next two years making it possible for
countries to enter the Economic and Monetary Union (EMU) smoothly,
an economic report predicts.
</P>
<P>
The Vienna Research Institute's report said the foreign trade
of most European countries has been increasing rapidly in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Europe's demand for and its manufacturing of goods would
increase 2.5 percent this year, the report added.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, Germany, France and Austria, whose economies were
considered rather sluggish, would record a growth rate of three
percent, the average rate for the European Union.
</P>
<P>
The report is equally optimistic about the economic prospects
for 1999, predicting that European economies will continue to grow
in 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
