<DOCNO> XIE19971202.0293 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nanning-Kunming Railway Line Opens to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The 898.7-km Nankun Railway
Line officially entered operations today.
</P>
<P>
The line runs from Nanning, capital of the Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region, to Kunming, capital of Yunnan Province, with a
trunk line running to Hongguo in Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
The railway, built at a cost of 20 billion-yuan (2.4 billion US
dollars), is the nation's most technically sophisticated railway
project. The line passes through perilous mountains and crosses
torrential rivers, with an altitude differential of more than
2,000 meters.
</P>
<P>
The line, which was constructed as part of China's strategy to
tap the economic potential of central and western areas, will
greatly benefit 15 million people, or a quarter of Chinese people
living below the poverty line. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
