<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Export More Tea This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan tea exports this
year are expected to rise by 12.3 percent, or 30 million
kilograms, compared with last year, tea industry sources said
today.
</P>
<P>
There had been significant orders from Iran, Britain, Iraq,
Russia and other buyers, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka's total tea exports last year were 244 million
kilograms. The exports during the first three quarters of this
year stood at 197 million kilograms, an eight percent increase
over the corresponding period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Most of the main buyers on the world market have increased
their purchases considerably this year, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Commonwealth of Independent States nations, including
Russia, alone have bought 40.9 million Sri Lankan tea so far this
year.
</P>
<P>
Tea is one of Sri Lanka's main export items and the source of
25 percent of its export earnings.  
</P>
</TEXT>
