<HEADLINE> Jiashi Recovers from Earthquakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Jiashi County in northwest
China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region is recovering from a
series of devastating earthquakes which have struck the area since
the beginning of this year, according to a local official.
</P>
<P>
Between January and April alone, the county recorded seven
quakes rated at above six on the Richter Scale. The devastating
earthquakes have claimed 22 lives and adversely affected well over
300,000 people. The quakes have destroyed 260,000 houses, and
caused direct economic loss of more than one billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The central government has allocated 117.9 million yuan for
relief efforts, and rushed in large amounts of coal, medicines and
food to the victims.
</P>
<P>
Some 13,000 families have moved into new housing, and damaged
schools and office buildings have been rebuilt.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the county have harvested over 142,000 tons of
grain and 25,000 tons of cotton.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
