<HEADLINE> Chile, EU to Forge Free Trade Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Trade officials from Chile and
the European Union (EU) started today a new round of talks to
forge a free trade agreement.
</P>
<P>
The work, by a joint sub-commission on trade, is scheduled to
begin with the review of the results reached by teams working on
issues of goods, services and trade.
</P>
<P>
Kicked off last year to pave the way for a final Chilean-EU
agreement, the project consists of several stages for progressive
liberalization of goods and services trade.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the two sides are also expected to analyze a
series of related agreements that involve sectors such as customs
assistance, public contracts and health matters.
</P>
<P>
These agreements, or sectoral accords, have reportedly entered
into different stages of negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The outcome of the ongoing sub-commission meeting are to be
studied Wednesday, when the Joint Commission of Chile and the
European Union gather again in Santiago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
