<HEADLINE> China Urges UNIDO to Do More to Help Developing Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Industrial
Development Organization (UNIDO) should do more to help the
developing countries, a Chinese official told the organization's
seventh session which opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Long Yongtu, head of the Chinese delegation, said that with
coordination as its key function, this Vienna-based agency should
promote prosperity for all countries and wipe out poverty across
the world.
</P>
<P>
Long, who serves as the chief negotiator of the Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation Ministry, said, "The world is developing
unevenly and the gap between the developed and developing
countries is further widened."
</P>
<P>
He hoped the organization will make fresh efforts in promoting
the transfer of advanced and practical industrial technologies to
the developing countries.
</P>
<P>
The UNIDO, founded in January 1967, now has more than 160
members. 
