<HEADLINE> Shangdong Improving Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 2 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shangdong Province
has achieved notable progress by placing priority on agriculture
during the process of national economic development.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the province has invested 17.2 billion
yuan (2.15 billion US dollars) in agriculture over the past five
years. Investments for 1996 hit 4.25 billion yuan (830 million US
dollars), up 39.8 percent on the figure for 1992.
</P>
<P>
The province has transformed 1.13 million ha. of low- to
medium-yield land, reclaimed wastelands covering 190,000 ha and
completed afforestation projects on an additional 130,000 hectares.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, the province has invested more than one billion
yuan to introduce over 60 improved varieties from both at home and
abroad, and promote the use of advanced cultivating technology.
</P>
<P>
Shandong has also invested five billion yuan over the past five
years to establish over 18,000 processing and marketing
enterprises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
