<HEADLINE> China's Weightlifters to Take Part in Thailand Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Weightlifting team
on Monday left for the men's 68th and women's 11th World
Weightlifting Championships to be held in Chiang Mai, Thailand
from December 6-14.
</P>
<P>
The event will be a farewell meeting for the present weight
categories in the sport since the International Weightlifting
Federation (IWF) has decided to introduce new divisions from
January first, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Under IWF's plan, the present 10 divisions in men's class will
be reduced to 8 featuring 56, 62, 69, 77, 85, 94,105 and above 105
kilograms while the women's 9 divisions will also be changed into
7, including 48, 53, 58, 63, 69, 75 and above 75.
</P>
<P>
The new system will be practised in the 2000 Sydney Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The farewell competition will be of historic significance to
strongmen and strongwomen if they can set new records. 
</P>
