<HEADLINE> Shanghai Plans Huangpu River Cableway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 2 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai tourism and
architectural experts are discussing the feasibility of building a
cableway spanning the Huangpu River which runs through the vast
metropolis in east China.
</P>
<P>
The cableway, dubbed the "Oriental Rainbow", will stretch
between two towers, one 155-meter tower in Puxi and a 65-meter
tower in Pudong.
</P>
