<HEADLINE> Argentina's Oil Production Up in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's oil production
is expected to go up to 46 million metric tons this year, a 5
percent surge over the 44 million tons of last year.
</P>
<P>
The output, as projected by latest official studies, is likely
to come along with natural gas production of 37 billion cubic
meters this year, against the 34 billion cubic meters last year.
</P>
<P>
The oil industry is Argentina's second largest foreign currency
earner following agriculture and cattle, which makes over 3.6
billion dollars in foreign sales, or 13 percent of total exports.
</P>
<P>
Argentina's oil reserves are up to 6.6 billion barrels,
equivalent to 14 years of its current production capacity.
</P>
<P>
Oil company workers and executives celebrated in November the
90th anniversary of their activity in Argentina. 
</P>
