chairman of the Board of Daimler-Benz of Germany, and the members
of the company's Board of International Advisers,
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji met with Raul Castro Ruz,
first vice-president of the Council of State and first
vice-president of the Council of Ministers of Cuba yesterday
afternoon, saying that the current China visit of Raul Castro has
been a complete success.
</P>
<P>
-- Wei Jianxing, a member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, has said that the
democratic system should be improved in rural areas by promoting
openness of village affairs.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China won praises from the United Nations yesterday for its
strenuous endeavor to keep the HIV/AIDS epidemic at a
comparatively low prevalence level.
</P>
<P>
-- Development of cross-Straits relations is paramount, and
central government officials are urging Taiwan's counties and
cities to help enhance these links.
</P>
