<HEADLINE> Russia, Ukraine's Parliaments to Approve Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Speakers of the Russian and
Ukrainian parliaments said today the Treaty of Friendship,
Cooperation and Partnership will be ratified by the two
parliaments at the end of the year, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Russian State Duma Chairman Gennady Seleznev met with visiting
Ukrainian Supreme Soviet Chairman Alexande Moroz and discussed the
approval of the treaty and parliamentary cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Moroz said "the simultaneous ratification" of the document will
further economic cooperation between the two countries. The treaty
was signed on May 31 by Russian President Boris Yeltsin and his
Ukrainian counterpart, Leonid Kucham.
</P>
<P>
On the status of the Russian language, Moroz said the languages
of Russian and Ukrainian had equal status in his country, and
Ukraine does not discriminate against the Russian language.
</P>
<P>
Seleznev agreed with Moroz's views, saying the two parliaments
should increase contacts in an effort to clear tariff barriers and
strengthen cooperation among CIS members.
</P>
<P>
The Ukrainian parliamentary delegation arrived here today.
</P>
