<HEADLINE> Havelange Praises World Cup Finals Preparation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- President Joao Havelange of FIFA,
world football govening body, Monday gave the thumbs-up sign to
the preparation of the World Cup finals in France next year in an
interview with the Fegallo.
</P>
<P>
The president, who will attend the draw ceremony of the 1998
World Cup finals to be held in Marseille, France on December 4,
took a rosy picture of the finals success.
</P>
<P>
The soccer chief crowned the soccer premiere competition with
the title " high-tech World Cup" , thinking that France's advanced
technology will make the event a great success.
</P>
<P>
Havelange praised the automatic metal fence as a "technical
wonder", which will rise up in case of emergency to separate
pitches from spectators.
</P>
<P>
FIFA has demanded that the fence around playgrounds as a
security measure should be removed to show respect to players'
personality.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the modification to games rules, Havelange held
strongly against footballers' scooping act and opposed the way
videos are used to judge matches.
</P>
<P>
The president said that in the coming finals every team has the
possibility of carrying off the palm, thinking that the form of
each team and chances are also deciding factors.
</P>
<P>
Havelange also expressed his regret that during his tenure
Africa failed to win a bid to host the World Cup, hoping that his
predecessor would offer a chance to the continent.
</P>
<P>
The president, who held the post for 24 years, is expected to
retire in June next year. 
</P>
