<HEADLINE> FIFA to Decide Eight Seeded Teams in World Cup Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The world soccer governing body
FIFA will decide on Tuesday the eight seeded teams in Thursday's
World Cup Draw on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Brazil and host team France have been
decided as two of the eight seeded teams, as well as three-time
world champions Germany who are also the reigning European
champions.
</P>
<P>
Italy, who qualified for the World Cup finals through the
playoffs, are also favored to be seeded in the Draw. But England,
who finished above Italy in their qualifying group, are unlikely
to be seeded.
</P>
<P>
FIFA will decide all the eight seeded teams according to their
World Cup records, especially the last three World Cups, in
conjunction with their positions in the latest FIFA rankings.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates include Argentina, Belgium, Spain, Mexico,
Romania, Bulgaria and so on. 
</P>
