<HEADLINE> China to Continue Work for Peace in Middle East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- China will continue to
work with the international community for peace and stability in
Middle East, its Permanent Representative to the United Nations
Qin Huasun said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the 52nd Session of U.N. General Assembly on the
question of Palestine, he said China calls on Israel to stop
building Jewish settlements in East Jerusalem and hopes that all
parties concerned will continue to take a flexible and pragmatic
approach toward the Middle East question.
</P>
<P>
China hopes that all parties will strictly observe and
implement the agreements already reached, fulfill earnestly their
obligations, remove obstruction and resume talks at an early date
on the basis of the relevant U.N. resolutions and the principle of
"land for peace" to push the peace process forward, he said.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Qin said Israel should refrain from enforcing
closure on the self-rule areas or freezing revenues of the
Palestinians at will.
</P>
<P>
Developed countries should undertake more obligations and carry
out at an early date the commitment they have already made so as
to facilitate early economic recovery and development in the
Palestinian self-rule areas, he said.
</P>
<P>
China will continue to provide assistance within its
capability for the Palestinian people through various channels
and contribute its share to the economic development in the
self-rule areas, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
