<HEADLINE> HK to Host 1st World Squash Doubles Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 2 (Xinhua) -- The inaugural World Squash
Doubles Championships are to be staged from December 10 to 14 at
the Hong Kong Football Club, Happy Valley here, organizers
announced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Participating in the championships are more than 50 players
from 14 countries and regions. Among them are world's top-ranked
Sarah Fitzgerald and fifth-ranked partner Carol Owens from
Australia, 10th-ranked Chris Walker and Mark Cairns from Britain,
and Pakistan's six-time world singles champion Jahangir Khan.
</P>
<P>
The event will be held on the newly-built doubles courts at the
club and the added features will be the erection of the clearview
portable squash court in the sports hall, which is up to
international standard.
</P>
<P>
The men's and women's doubles events will each have 12 teams,
which are pooled into Groups A and B for preliminaries. Top two
teams from each group advance into the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
The mixed doubles event will see single knock-out play among
the 10 teams.
</P>
<P>
The total prize money for the championships is set for 400,000
HK dollars (51,200 US dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
