<HEADLINE> German Private Banks Have Share in Nazi Gold: Reports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 1 (Xinhua) -- The gold robbed by German Nazis
from eastern European Jews between 1942 and 1945 had been partly
transferred by the Nazi German central bank to the country's
private banks, German television reports said today.
</P>
<P>
According to the ARD television network, the new foundings were
achieved after the first examination of the microfilms found in
Vienna last week, which included some photocopies of original
documents and files of the Nazi central bank -- Reichsbank.
</P>
<P>
The gold, worth about 1.4 billion German marks (790 million
U.S. dollars) today, was addressed to the Deutsche Bank and the
Dresdner Bank, Germany's two largest commercial banks, the report
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
