<HEADLINE> Jiang Lays Wreath at Mexican Monument to National </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang
Zemin today laid a wreath at the Monument to National Heroes to
commemorate those who dedicated their lives to Mexico's national
independence.
</P>
<P>
Jiang laid the wreath solemnly at the base of monument and
stood in silence for a moment, before a military band played the
Mexican national anthem for ceremony and soldiers fired shots.
</P>
<P>
The ribbons on the wreath read: "Immortal are the National
Heroes" and "The National Heroes who Sacrificed Their Lives for
the Independence of Mexico Will Live in the Heart of the People
Forever."
</P>
<P>
The monument, located in downtown Mexico City, was erected in
1952 to commemorate six young soldiers who died in a battle
against U.S. aggressors in 1847.  
