<HEADLINE> UNICEF Chief Urges Expanded Steps to Combat Aids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"With children increasing at risk from HIV/AIDS, there is an
urgent need to expanded programmes of treatment and protection,
including education and AIDS awareness training", Bellamy
said.
</P>
<P>
Bellamy stressed that awareness of the problem of how children and
young people are affected by HIV/AIDS must be built by promoting
the principles enshrined in the United Nations Convention of the
Rights of the Child; by disseminating information to young
people on the risks of transmission and methods of protection;
and by offering education and services in sexual health.
</P>
<P>
