<HEADLINE> Canada, EU to Hold Summit This Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean
Chretien announced today that a Canada-European Union (EU)
Transatlantic Summit will be held here on December 4.
</P>
<P>
Jean-Claude Juncker, prime minister of Luxembourg and president
of European Council, and Jacques Santer, president of the European
Commission, will attend the summit.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, the second since the Canada-EU Political
Declaration and Action Plan was signed a year ago, will provide an
opportunity to assess progress achieved and to enhance cooperation
between the two sides, Chretien said.
</P>
<P>
The summit is expected to discuss certain bilateral issues,
such as tariff and non-tariff barriers, as well as trade
liberalization between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two sides is also expected to sign an
agreement on customs cooperation and mutual assistance, according
to a news release from Chretien's office. 
