<HEADLINE> Bosnian Peace Conference to Be Held in Bonn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Bonn will play host to an
international conference to review the implementation of the
Dayton peace accord for Bosnia on December 9-10.
</P>
<P>
German officials said today that German Foreign Minister Klaus
Kinkel and his French counterpart Hubert Vedrine will make a joint
trip to Sarajevo on Thursday to prepare for the ministerial
meeting which is expected to be attended by 51 countries and 21
international organizations.
</P>
<P>
The annual review conference, already met twice in London, will
examine the implementation of the Dayton peace accord by the
former warring parties and will give new impetus to a
"self-sustainable" political and economic development in Bosnia,
officials in Bonn said. 
