<HEADLINE> Chirac Wishes France to Become "World Cultural Center" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
today expressed his wish that France will become "the cultural
center of the world" which he said once was for nearly seven
centuries through its sciences and culture.
</P>
<P>
"This should be our ambition, this is a question of political
will," said Chirac at a ceremony of the Academy of Sciences of
France for rewarding a medal to the Belgian biologist Jozef Schell.
</P>
<P>
Chirac called on French scientists to contribute more in the
field of modern technology, the fight against infectious diseases
and the control of greenhouse gases.
</P>
<P>
He also recalled the "principles that France, with the
European Union, will defend tomorrow at the Kyoto" international
conference on control of emission of greenhouse gases, which began
today in the ancient Japanese city.
</P>
<P>
"At the present rhythm (of increase of pollution), our
children risk to live in a disfigured world," he added. 
