<HEADLINE> NATO Secretary General to Visit France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 1 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General of the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) Javier Solana will make a
visit to France from Wednesday evening, during which he will hold
talks with French President Jacques Chirac.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse (AFP) quoted sources at the NATO
headquarters in Brussels as saying today that Solana will also
attend a plenary session of the Western European Union on Thursday
and will meet with French Defense Minister Alain Richard.
</P>
<P>
France's full reintegration into the NATO integrated structure
is suspended because of its failure to have the Americans give up
a key military command seat in the southern wing of the alliance.
</P>
<P>
France gave its green light to the NATO plan of expansion to
central and eastern Europe at the Madrid summit in June, but
refused to return to its integrated military command structure,
from which it withdrew in 1966.
</P>
<P>
So far the NATO allies have not presented any new proposals for
helping France reach a compromise with the United States over the
Naples-based Southern Command of NATO, which wishes to take over.
</P>
</TEXT>
